snippet.textDisplay:
We are only seeing what the producers want us to see with this programme. Mark came across as very controlling here but we dont know the reason behind this. He looked like he was at the end of his tether with Kenya and it was just a matter of time before he, she or they decided to part company. Whilst I feel for the baby, she is too young to understand what is going on right now but hopefully they can settle their differences and be great collaborative parents.

That all said, I do believe in karma...and Kenya has exhibited vile behaviours throughout her tenure on this show and beyond. I think back to her god awful behaviour with Vivica, which resulted in Vivica having to read her. I am not a fan of hers and personally she has ingrained issues that she needs several couch sessions to address. It's the classic 'what comes around...goes around and bites your arse off'
